Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potatoes{2} into 2cm wide wedges (no
need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle},
season with @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch} then toss to coat. Spread out
in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Finely chop the @coriander{1}(finely chopped, stalks and all). Zest and halve the
@lime{1}(zested and halved). Pop the lime zest, @Thai style spice mix{1%portion},
and half the coriander into a large #bowl{}. Mix in the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} and
@soy sauce{12.5%ml}. Add the @British beef mince{240%g}. Season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}, then mix together with your hands. Roll the mince into
even-sized balls then shape into 1cm thick burgers (1 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a lightly oiled baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of
your oven until cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

While the burgers cook, halve the @red chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways, deseeded and
finely chopped), finely chop the @salted peanuts{15%g}. In a #medium bowl{}, combine
half the lime juice with the remaining @soy sauce{12.5%ml}, remaining coriander,
half the peanuts and half the chilli. Add a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} then set the
dressing aside.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}(halved lengthways, thinly sliced) then thinly slice
the @spring onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Just before serving, pop the sliced
baby gem into the bowl with the soy dressing. Mix well to coat the salad.

Share the burger patties and sweet potato wedges between your plates. Pop the baby
gem salad on the side and sprinkle the spring onion, the remaining peanuts and
remaining chilli all over. Chop any remaining lime into wedges for squeezing over.
Enjoy!